messages.content: Unlimited power!
quite limited, actually
This powe could be any uncommon power
All uncommon powers i know are iron fortress
Iron fortress gut
I close my case
Broadly speaking would you take this if you need scaling or you're hoping to highroll into some OP synergy?
hoping for real scaling from an uncommon power will just leave you disappointed
I've tried it out before and ended up with several utility powers and several other synergy-specific powers
so literally it's just for if you're looking for a specific card
It sure is one of the unidentified cards for snecko.

cards pretty great, most powers in downfall are very strong and the 4 default characters have some good pulls to. Your quite likely to get a usable card to use in every fight and have a chance to get a run winning power you can ID. Taking several of these, 3 cost and rare power are often the easiest win routes for snecko
you have better luck than I do

your not trying to get demon form in every fight, just getting an average power like infinite wards or brawl is fine most of the time; of course the abitily to take a run winning power if one shows up is pretty good
power stacking in general is pretty good because you only have a 1/5 change to hit your act 3 boss that punishes you for doing that (and even vs defect 3 its fine to play like 4 powers)
defect 3 doesn't punish you for mass powers that hard
just don't play them before turn 2
then it's fine
depends on your damage or block really, if you can just kill the boss before he plays multicast again then it sorta doesnt matter
and tbf most characters can achieve that
demon form would be an impressive pull from an uncommon power
ya it would be :flawed:
I just mean your not trying to get the best cards every time because thats not realistic; you just want cards that you can use
the best pulls this has are probably, feel no pain, dark embrace, third seal, fourth seal and max output
the worst pulls arnt usually dead cards; but theres some (defect, hermit and watcher have several. Thats without the horseshoe relic of course)

watcher's dead cards are rushdown and mental fortress?
